Francisco d’Anconia is an enormously wealthy and brilliant industrialist, Francisco is the first to join Galt’s strike and the man who pays the highest price for it, losing his first and only love, Dagny. Francisco works as the strike’s most active recruiter, focusing much of his attention on Rearden. By pretending to be a worthless playboy, Francisco is able to hide his efforts to destroy d’Anconia copper and thereby keep it out of the hands of the looters.